Inside the plane, there were no human remains.
Wooden County Commissioner John Anderson said: “The plane has been located, we have sent a squadron, and now we have confirmation that it is proper to what Steve Fossett was flying over on the day of his disappearance.”
The commissioner said no human remains have been found on or around the plane.
The 63-year-old billionaire was found dead in February.
